ğŸš€ Getting Started
Command	Description
terraform init	Initialize a Terraform project (downloads provider plugins, sets up state)
terraform version	Show Terraform version
terraform fmt	Format Terraform code properly
terraform validate	Check configuration for syntax and logic errors

ğŸ“¦ Plan & Apply Infrastructure
Command	Description
terraform plan	Show what will be created/changed/destroyed
terraform apply	Apply the plan and provision infrastructure
terraform apply -auto-approve	Apply without asking for confirmation
terraform destroy	Destroy all managed infrastructure
terraform destroy -auto-approve	Destroy without confirmation

ğŸ“„ State Management
Command	Description
terraform show	Show the current state
terraform state list	List resources in state
terraform state show <resource>	Show details of a specific resource
terraform state rm <resource>	Remove a resource from the state file

ğŸ§  Workspaces (for environments)
Command	Description
terraform workspace list	List all workspaces
terraform workspace new <name>	Create a new workspace
terraform workspace select <name>	Switch to a workspace

ğŸ“¥ Modules & Providers
Command	Description
terraform get	Download modules mentioned in config
terraform providers	Show providers used in configuration

ğŸ” Secrets and Variables
Command	Description
terraform output	Show output values from state
terraform output <name>	Show a specific output
terraform apply -var="key=value"	Pass variable values directly
terraform apply -var-file="vars.tfvars"	Load variable values from a file


